<item>BLUFF</item>
<item>VERTIGINOUS</item></list><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">陡</item><item xml:lang="och">陡</item></list>
<div type="definition">
<p>INTENSELY SLANTED so as to be DIFFICULT TO ASCEND OR DESCEND on it.</p></div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general word is dǒu 陡 (ant. píng 平 "level").</p>
<p>2. Qiào 峭 (ant. yí 夷 "level") describes a dramatic form of precipitous territory.</p>
<p>3. Chán 巉 describes a high degree of precipitous proclivity in a poetic manner.</p>
<p>4. Jùn 峻 refers to precipitous height.</p></div>
